# Vercel prod deploy (GramWise / fixload)

## Fact

**`git push` does not update production** unless the Vercel project is linked to GitHub with auto-deploy. This repo currently uses **manual CLI deploy** to `https://fixload.vercel.app`.

## When to deploy

After any **important** change that must be visible in prod:

- UI (`app/`, `globals.css`)
- i18n, wizard session, recipe/fixed-charges/results flows
- API routes (`app/api/`)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` or Stripe env-dependent behavior

Skip deploy for docs-only / `.cursor/` / engine-only (no app rebuild needed) unless the user asks.

## Agent procedure (mandatory after push)

When implementation is committed and pushed to `main` (or user says deploy / prod / vercel):

1. From repo root: `npx vercel deploy --prod --yes`
2. Wait until deploy is **READY** and aliased to `fixload.vercel.app`
3. Tell the user: deployment URL + « hard refresh » (Ctrl+F5) on `/recipe` if UI changed

Do **not** assume GitHub Actions or Pages updated Vercel — they are separate.

## Env changes

If production env vars changed in Vercel dashboard, redeploy even without code changes.

## Optional (user setup, not agent)

Link **Vercel → Git → `gramwise` repo → Production branch `main`** so future pushes auto-deploy and this CLI step can be skipped.
